                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Clear all of this block's properties and children.

Continue while the given stream is not at the end.

Read the next XML element.

Check to see if it is a start element.

Get its tag name and check to see if it begins with an underscore and is therefore a property.

Get the property key and set this block's property with the text enclosed in the XML tag if the key is a valid property.

Else this is the start tag of a child block.

Create a new child block with the type encoded within the tag name, call its set to XML method using the given stream, and then append it to this block as a new child.

Else if this is the end element for this block then break out of the reading loop.
</__p_inlines>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>stream</__p_name>
